the more difficult, she was a hothead, inheritated from one of her mothers.  She knew her trainers knew about this and played on it time and time again.  A good warrior keeps their cool.  That was the one skill she never aquired and this was the one she had to have to become a warrior.  And then after that of course every warrior aspired to join the Queen's royal guard.  Dressing her soft leathers she slide her mother's sword into the scabbard on her back and looked into the polished glass.::  Well I guess its time to learn a little control.  ::sighing she pulled on a heavy cloak to ward off the cool morning air.  She'd get a quick run in before meeting with the rest of the initates:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uwarriorquinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarriorQuinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#993300>(1/21/01 9:55:07 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/az/RaesHomepage/gallery2.html WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Warriors Big Day</span><hr size=1> ::Quinn stumbled back into the initiates huts and fell into her bed.  For all her bluster and bravado, today had totally kicked her butt.  It seemed to her that the trainers worked her harder then the other girls.  Maybe it was because all the other girls kept becoming preoccupied watching Quinn work.  She knew of her reputation with the younger initiates and she didn't mind one bit.  She was young and not out looking for a lifemate, so why not just have some fun.  After a few minutes of laying on her bed, she dragged herself up and started to unhook her sheath and sword.  Startled when one of the trainers burst into the hut, yelling::Everyone up and outside in two minutes.  ::Quinn wasn't sure she heard the woman right.  They had been out working hard all day, and now they were going out again.  Grumbling she hooked her sheath back and stood a little unsteady at first.:: Just remember, Elite Guard, Elite Guard. ::trudging outside to fall into line:: <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uwarriorquinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarriorQuinn</A> at: 1/21/01 12:45:20 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uwarriorquinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarriorQuinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#993300>(1/21/01 12:53:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.angelfire.com/az/RaesHomepage/gallery2.html WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Warriors Big Day</span><hr size=1> ::they had been released for a &quot;nap&quot; around mid-morning and were told to get up in enough time to have the noon meal.  Quinn hadn't even been giving time early to break her fast, so a noon meal was just what the healer ordered, other then a few more hours of sleep.  She woke in enough time to dunk her head in a rain barrel and clean up just a bit.  After making herself presentable she made her way across the village toward the feast hall.  She glanced around at the various Amazons milling around and cursed herself that she hadn't taken the time to really get to know any of them.  Granted she saw the stares from the younger girls.  But again, she didn't mind those, it just helped to up her already inflated ego.  But she would have liked to get to know a few of her peers.  Even living in a communal village could be lonely.  But again, she had a goal and that was to become a warrior and friendships might just get in the way at this point.  Walking into the feast hall she quickly filled a plate, then found a fairly empty area to eat. She knew she'd have to be quick to be ready for the rest of her second day in training hell.:: <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uwarriorquinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarriorQuinn</A> at: 1/21/01 1:14:26 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uwarriorquinn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WarriorQuinn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>registered user</span><br>  Posts: 4<br> <font color=#993300>(1/23/01 2:41:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> A Warrior's Big Day</span><hr size=1> ::After an uneventful Quinn made her way back over to the training field. The afternoon was to be spent with chobos, one of her favorite weapons.  Problem was she had seemed to pick up a competitor.  One of the younger girls had decided she wanted top spot in the class and that meant taking it away from Quinn.  There had been snide comments all day, which to her own amazement, Quinn ignored.  Things were going fairly well and then the trainers decided to have a nice friendly competition.  Quinn went 100% in each round and at the end found herself facing her antagonist .  With a deep breath Quinn tried to get herself focused on the match and ignored the girls dirty looks.  Quinn turned around to take her chobos from a young girl that had been smiling her way all day, when she heard the comment.:: I heard that Quinn didn't even have the nerve to avenge her poor mothers murder, such a shame.  ::Quinn had had enough and turned quickly charging the girl and tackling her around the waist.  The trainers stood back for a few moments to see how this played out.  Quinn had gotten a good hold on the girl and was about to slam a large fist into her face, when she got an eyeful of dirt.  She pulled back and tried to wipe her eyes, but the punch to her eye flung her backwards.  Still wiping her eyes, she pulled herself up onto her knees, when she felt a blow with a chobo to her side and then an uppercut with the weapon to her jaw.  She laid on her back panting in pain and awaited the next blow, but it didn't come.  The trainers had seen the other girl throw the dirt in her eyes and rushed over to restrain her.:: Help Quinn up and to the healers hut.  ::The head trainer said.  Quinn shadow went to help her up when her hand was pushed away and Quinn pulled herself to her feet on her own.  With a determined look through blurry eyes she strode right past everyone and made her way for her own hut.  At least today wasn't going to be a total blow out.  They still had the festival and she might just see Ainia again, if she was lucky.:: <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/spinningsword.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Vasilissa</span><br>  Posts: 214<br> <font color=#993300>(1/23/01 3:26:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitesistersofthemiscrya.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=133.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/pleiade3/ehipp.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: A Warrior's Big Day</span><hr size=1> :::Hippolyte had been watching the training from the distance.  She knew the training could be hard.  And especially hard for one who was new to the village.  Many young warriors had grown up together in the village and already made their small groups.  These groups were important when it came to wars.  But, Hipp also knew these groups made it tougher on those new to the village.  The new initiates would be tested to the core.  Hipp watched as Quinn had her scrimish with the one girl.  She was far enough away not to be noticed that she was watching.  But, that also made her far enough away, that she could not hear what was being said.  As Quinn walked away from the group, Hipp cocked a brow.  Her brown eyes watching the young warrior's path::: <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::>
